						<div class="postbody">Zelda 2 was made of 4x16 wide rooms, and allowed up to 64 of them per bank.  There were 8 banks of levels, but not all rooms were used, and not all were full width.
<br />Plus there's the overworld maps too.
<br />
<br />Oracle of ages had 10x8 maps, on a 14x14 grid, and 4 overworlds.  Plus 28 floors of dungeons, each map 15x11, and each floor up to 8x8 if filled.  But that's not a NES game.</div>

					
